research_question: Does VQE accuracy improve on Tuna-9's best qubit pair [2,4] (92.3% Bell fidelity) vs [0,1] (87.0%)? The daemon-001 run on [0,1] gave -1.1222 Ha (9.45 kcal/mol error). If qubit quality is the bottleneck, [2,4] should be significantly better.
description: VQE H2 at equilibrium (R=0.735) on best qubit pair [2,4]. Same Hamiltonian and optimal alpha as daemon-001 but better qubits. Direct comparison of qubit quality impact on VQE.
